headlines.description: — Tyrese Haliburton had 22 points and 11 assists, Myles Turner added 20 points and 10 rebounds and the Indiana Pacers beat Charlotte 125-113 on Wednesday on night in which Hornets All-Star guard LaMelo Ball re-injured his left ankle after stepping on...
headlines.shortLinkText: Haliburton, Pacers beat Hornets; Ball re-injures ankle

headlines.description: — Anthony Edwards scored 35 points, Karl-Anthony Towns added 30 and the Minnesota Timberwolves built a 27-point lead in the first half in a 126-108 victory over the Orlando Magic on Wednesday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Edwards, Towns lead Timberwolves to rout of Magic, 126-108

events.name: Oklahoma City Thunder at Washington Wizards

headlines.description: — Shai Gilgeous-Alexander hit a 3-pointer with 1.1 seconds remaining and matched a career high with 42 points as the Oklahoma City Thunder beat the Washington Wizards 121-120 on Wednesday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Gilgeous-Alexander nets 42, hits winner as OKC beats Wizards

headlines.description: — The Boston Celtics were missing two key members of their rotation.
headlines.shortLinkText: Celtics claim 8th straight win, beat Hawks 126-101

headlines.description: — O.G. Anunoby scored a season-high 32 points and matched his season high with 10 rebounds and the Toronto Raptors used a 21-0 run in the third quarter to beat Miami 112-104 on Wednesday night, ending the Heat’s winning streak at three.
headlines.shortLinkText: Anunoby has season-high 32 points, Raptors beat Heat 112-104

headlines.description: — Brook Lopez understands that playing alongside Giannis Antetokounmpo is going to create plenty of open looks.
headlines.shortLinkText: Lopez scores 29, Bucks deal Cavs 5th straight loss 113-98

events.name: Chicago Bulls at New Orleans Pelicans

headlines.description: — CJ McCollum scored 23 points, Jonas Valanciunas added 22 and the New Orleans Pelicans won their second straight game without Zion Williamson in the lineup, beating the Chicago Bulls 124-110 on Wednesday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: CJ McCollum scores 23 points, Pelicans top Bulls 124-110

headlines.description: — Kevin Porter Jr. had 17 points and 11 rebounds and eight assists, and the last-place Houston Rockets took advantage of Luka Doncic's absence in a 101-92 victory over the Dallas Mavericks on Wednesday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Porter, Rockets beat Mavericks 101-92 with Doncic resting

events.name: New York Knicks at Denver Nuggets

headlines.description: — Julius Randle scored a season-high 34 points and the New York Knicks took advantage of Nikola Jokic's absence to win in Denver for the first time in 16 years, rallying past the Nuggets 106-103 on Wednesday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Knicks rally, end skid against Jokic-less Nuggets, 106-103

events.name: Golden State Warriors at Phoenix Suns

headlines.description: — Devin Booker stepped back for a 3-pointer in the closing minute of the third quarter as Golden State's Stephen Curry gamely tried to stay with him, putting a hand in his face. Booker made the shot anyway as a frustrated Curry dropped his head.
headlines.shortLinkText: Curry scores 50 points, but Suns beat Warriors 130-119
